<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c00">Even if I know my current branch, having my prompt show me untracked&#x2F;uncommitted&#x2F;unpushed changes helps to identify if something didn’t work because I’m in a dirty state, or if something I ran (unexpectedly) caused a dirty state.<p>For example, I don’t expect running scripts&#x2F;build.sh to modify tracked files in the repo.  Seeing part of the prompt go from “” to “?2!3” (two untracked, three changed files) makes that glaringly obvious.</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=44368918&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44364874%2344368918" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr>
