<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c00">With or without starship, one problem I have with zsh prompts is that when I press Enter, there is still a visible delay where for a fraction of a second, the cursor moves to the beginning of the next line.<p>This makes a nasty &quot;flashing&quot; effect.<p>If I keep Enter pressed, the cursor is permanently visible at offset 0 in the lowest line.<p>If the prompt is ultra-fast (e.g. plain root shell prompt on zsh), it happens less (e.g. only 50% of cases), but as soon as the prompt does anything, it&#x27;s very visible.<p>I observe this with many terminals (gnome-terminal, wezterm, kitty, alacritty, xterm).<p>The only terminal I tried that doesn&#x27;t have this problem is urxvt, where it looks perfect.<p>Video repro: <a href="https:&#x2F;&#x2F;nh2.me&#x2F;flashing-cursors-on-newline.mp4" rel="nofollow">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;nh2.me&#x2F;flashing-cursors-on-newline.mp4</a><p>Why, and is there a way around it for those other terminals?</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=44371598&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44364874%2344371598" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr>
